House Democratic budget writers hopeto win budget committee approval of a budget package to cut thedeficit more than 36 billion dlrs perhaps as early as tomorrow,committee sources said.    After several weeks of closed sessions, Democrats are readyto present to the full committee tomorrow a package to cut thecongressionally estimated 171 billion dlr deficit in 1988 byabout 36 billion dlrs, half through revenues.    The plan could cut 9 billion dlrs from defence spendinglevels of 290.5 billion and 9 billion dlrs from many domesticprograms, excluding Social Security. Reuter&#3;